00:20:39,580 --> 00:20:41,920
-我没兴趣  -我不觉得
- I'm not interested. - Beg to differ.

365
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,820
拜托别拿老记者的那套来压我
And spare me the seasoned journalist routine, please.

366
00:20:44,940 --> 00:20:46,740
你在这行干了30年
Your 30 years in the business.

367
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:49,390
我跟你的老助理安吉拉谈过
I've spoken to your old assistant, Angela.

368
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:52,130
她写了一篇关于与你共事的报道
She's written a piece about her time with you.

369
00:20:52,530 --> 00:20:53,870
我可以发布  也可以...
I could run it, or...

370
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:58,810
你曾经对弗兰克·安德伍德像狗一般紧咬不放
Your dogged pursuit of Frank Underwood, pardon the pun,

371
00:20:58,810 --> 00:21:00,930
现在改追着他的女人了
is now your pursuit of his bride.

372
00:21:05,420 --> 00:21:06,450
想想吧
Think about it.

373
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:12,370
你这年纪的男人  如今都很容易崩溃
Men your age, they unravel very easily these days.

374
00:21:15,990 --> 00:21:18,560
文森特·阿布佐法官有资质
Judge Vincent Abruzzo has the credentials.

375
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:20,970
有发表论著  有公开声明
The published writings, the public statements.

376
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:23,480
全都没问题  都齐了
It all checks out. Full package.

377
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:26,390
所以你为什么迟迟不决定啊  总统女士
So what's the hesitation, Madam Prez?

378
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,020
为什么不认命阿布佐

379
00:21:26,390 --> 00:21:29,030
首都电视是加德纳分析的子公司
Beltway Television is owned by Gardner Analytics.

380
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:31,390
是邓肯·谢泼德的最新创造
It's the latest brainchild of Duncan Shepherd.

381
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:32,230
我已经回避了一切
So far, I've deflected

382
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:34,560
关于科鲁兹小姐言论的问题
all questions regarding Ms. Cruz's commentary.

383
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,810
很好  不要回应她
Good. Let's not dignify it.

384
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:47,290
行了  谢谢
No. That's fine, thank you.

385
00:21:49,010 --> 00:21:51,320
就是有这个问题  但我忍不住
They were a hazard, I couldn't resist.

386
00:21:54,020 --> 00:21:57,060
抱歉我没参加葬礼  还念《诗篇》了吗
Sorry I missed the funeral. Were there psalms?

387
00:21:57,060 --> 00:21:58,390
第42段
Number 42.

388
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:00,340
我喜欢那个
I love 42.

389
00:22:03,870 --> 00:22:06,550
纳泽不该直接找到你
Nasser had no business coming to you directly.

390
00:22:07,870 --> 00:22:10,570
我知道如果我见他  你就会突然出现
Well, I knew if I met with him, you'd suddenly appear.

391
00:22:10,910 --> 00:22:12,870
他觉得被骗了  简
He feels lied to, Jane.

392
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,360
因为确实如此
Because he was.

393
00:22:14,950 --> 00:22:18,260
我们根本没打算给那些土匪一席位置
We were never gonna give those bandits a seat at the table.

394
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:21,280
简  他威胁说哈里发国会再发动袭击
Jane, he's threatened more ICO attacks.

395
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:23,950
哈里发国基本上都被消灭了
ICO is neutralized, mostly.

396
00:22:23,990 --> 00:22:26,620
我们该重新考虑在叙利亚的行动了
It's time to re-think our involvement in Syria.

397
00:22:26,620 --> 00:22:28,310
撤军  重建
Stand down, rebuild.

398
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:32,020
这个协议对于我们所有人都很重要
This deal is important for all of us.

399
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:33,850
包括谢泼德兄妹
Including the Shepherds.

400
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,100
我也不喜欢他们家族
Look, I'm no fan of that family,

401
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:40,250
但在叙利亚问题上  我们的利益是一致的
but in the case of Syria, our interests align.

402
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:41,810
我们下一阶段
The next phase of our...

403
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:43,670
在该地区的行动
presence in the region

404
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:47,260
更多是为了战利品而不是和平了
is more about the spoils than the peace.

405
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,260
问题在于佩特罗夫
The problem is Petrov,

406
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:51,340
谢泼德兄妹和我都鄙视他
whom the Shepherds and I despise.

407
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:53,190
你有谢泼德家族什么把柄
What do you have on the Shepherds?

408
00:22:53,870 --> 00:22:56,070
跟你有联系的那几家机构
I'm sure one of the several agencies you're

409
00:22:56,070 --> 00:22:57,860
肯定有一家有料
involved with has something.

410
00:22:58,090 --> 00:23:00,730
你不是给每个和你打交道的人都建立份档案吗
And don't you keep files on everyone you're dealing with?

411
00:23:01,260 --> 00:23:03,360
比尔和安奈特都很小心
Bill and Annette are very careful.

412
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:05,560
那安奈特的儿子邓肯呢
What about Annette's son, Duncan?

413
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:09,740
马克比我更了解他们
Well, Mark knows them more than I do.

414
00:23:13,620 --> 00:23:16,750
我觉得对于前总统还有更好的选择
I thought there were better options for a former president...

415
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,500
但安奈特不肯放过弗兰克
but Annette wouldn't leave Frank alone.

416
00:23:22,340 --> 00:23:24,500
那就是他们的问题  他们不知何时该收手
That's their problem, they don't know when to stop.

417
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:27,900
你三个月前离开时
You know, when you left three months ago,

418
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:29,460
我还想你去了哪
I wondered where you'd gone.

419
00:23:31,130 --> 00:23:34,560
然后  我就再没想你了
And then, I didn't think of you at all.

420
00:23:36,590 --> 00:23:37,710
你那么说
You say that.

421
00:23:39,040 --> 00:23:42,130
但我在你的眼里看到了痛苦  总统女士
But I detect pain in your eyes, Madam President.

422
00:23:44,370 --> 00:23:47,400
就像渴望甘泉的小鹿
As a deer longs for streams of water.

423
00:23:47,780 --> 00:23:49,840
我如此渴望你  上帝
So I long for you, God.

424
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:52,150
你想他吗
Do you miss him?

425
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:56,250
上帝吗  总在想
God? Always.

426
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:05,180
我希望你搬到白宫里来跟我住  简
I'd like you to move in here with me, Jane, into the White House.

427
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:06,870
我需要你的建议
I need your counsel

428
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:10,390
以及你对马克的了解
and your perspective when it comes to Mark.

429
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,600
事实上  去年一整年在白宫
The truth is that whole last year in the White House...

430
00:24:17,770 --> 00:24:19,490
我完全迷失了
I just lost myself.

431
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:24,690
最疯狂的是  我都没见过佐伊·巴恩斯
And the crazy thing is, I've never even met Zoe Barnes.

432
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:27,090
你也这么跟联邦检察官说的吗
Is that what you told the US Attorney?

433
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:29,550
还是你和克莱尔·安德伍德做了交易
Or did you and Claire Underwood make a deal?

434
00:24:29,790 --> 00:24:31,720
我和总统分道扬镳了
The president and I are on different paths.

435
00:24:32,990 --> 00:24:34,600
你是说你没见过她
You're saying you haven't seen her.

436
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,530
我们谈过
We've spoken.

437
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:39,730
我就是不觉得她的白宫里有我的位置
I just don't see a role for me in her White House.

438
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,760
我在给科尔议员工作
I'm working with Congressman Cole.

439
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:47,290
他要竞选议长
He's making a play for speaker.

440
00:24:53,940 --> 00:24:55,430
我今天从《先驱报》辞职了
I left the Herald today.

441
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:00,110
如果你是为了这个找我
If that's why you wanted to see me,

442
00:25:00,110 --> 00:25:02,230
-想让我给你的新老板做报道  -不是
- make a pitch for your new guy. - No.

443
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:05,170
不  这是在做弥补
No, this is about making amends.

444
00:25:05,230 --> 00:25:07,660
-我去年秋天又开始喝酒了  -不
- Last fall I started drinking again. - No.

445
00:25:07,830 --> 00:25:08,650
你选这里
You picked this place

446
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:11,250
是因为这里到处是博主和国会山的鼠辈
because it's full of bloggers and Hill rats.

447
00:25:11,390 --> 00:25:14,740
现在  这里的人都能看到我们在说话
Right now, everyone here can see us talking together,

448
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:16,070
客客气气的
like civilized people.

449
00:25:16,070 --> 00:25:18,680
就好像我不曾在报纸上喊你"杀人犯"
As if I never called you a murderer in print.

450
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:25,150
你最新一篇关于弗兰西斯的报道
Your latest article on Francis.

451
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,290
关于他死前的几晚
This story about the nights leading up to his death?

452
00:25:27,290 --> 00:25:30,470
-你想弥补吗  -你的消息源是谁
- You want to make amends? - Who are your sources?

453
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:32,060
彼得·罗素
Peter Russo.

454
00:25:32,950 --> 00:25:34,290
佐伊·巴恩斯
Zoe Barnes.

455
00:25:34,860 --> 00:25:36,280
莉安·哈维
LeAnn Harvey.

456
00:25:40,060 --> 00:25:45,010
道格  你已经没有阴影可躲了
Doug, there isn't a shadow for you to hide in anymore.

457
00:25:45,830 --> 00:25:48,400
唯一知道一切的人  就是你
The only person knows everything is you.

458
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:49,740
我不全知道
I don't.

459
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,280
放弃他吧
Let him go.

460
00:25:57,910 --> 00:25:59,450
我不知道你什么意思
I don't know what you're talking about.

461
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:06,020
你早晚得做出决定
At some point, you're gonna have to decide.

462
00:26:08,290 --> 00:26:11,150
克莱尔·安德伍德  相信我
Claire Underwood, believe me,

463
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,050
等时候到了  她会找上你的
she'll come for you when it's time.

464
00:26:16,540 --> 00:26:17,590
谢谢
Thanks.

465
00:26:30,850 --> 00:26:32,600
那玩意有咖啡因的
You know, there's caffeine in that.

466
00:26:33,810 --> 00:26:34,740
我知道
I do.

467
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:39,540
我喜欢你爱喝阿诺德·帕尔默  但...
I love that you love Arnold Palmers, but--

468
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:41,930
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}指发明这种饮品的高尔夫球手

469
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:41,930
他可是个伟人
Arnold Palmer was a great man.

470
00:26:44,370 --> 00:26:46,290
还在想她吗
She still on your mind?

471
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:52,770
这样下去不行
This arrangement isn't working.

472
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:56,140
怎样
Which arrangement?

473
00:26:57,290 --> 00:26:58,770
马克  到床上来
Mark, come to bed.

474
00:27:01,080 --> 00:27:03,890
她得觉得自己有点自主权
She needs to feel some degree of autonomy.

475
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:05,420
去他的自主权
Fuck autonomy.

476
00:27:05,470 --> 00:27:07,280
她要为我们服务
She serves at our pleasure.

477
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:09,090
她肯定觉得自己不受重视
I'm sure she feels undervalued.

478
00:27:09,260 --> 00:27:10,440
不受重视
Undervalued?

479
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:12,850
克莱尔·黑尔  得了
Claire Hale? Please.

480
00:27:12,850 --> 00:27:14,420
要是比尔不能好起来呢
What if Bill doesn't get better?

481
00:27:18,030 --> 00:27:19,320
他好多了
He is better.

482
00:27:20,690 --> 00:27:22,200
如果在明面上
If we don't play this right,

483
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:24,660
我们不能做好  就注定要失败
in the public eye, we are doomed to fail.

484
00:27:24,660 --> 00:27:27,010
-你明白吧  -是她要完蛋
- You know that, right? - She's doomed, you mean.

485
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:27,940
听着
Look...

486
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:30,940
我们说清楚
Let's be clear.

487
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:35,000
我对她没有感觉  但她得把我视为伙伴
I am not attracted to her, but she needs to see me as a partner.

488
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:37,490
而且急什么
And what is the rush?

489
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:40,620
比尔要法庭的多数支持
Bill wants a majority on the court.

490
00:27:40,620 --> 00:27:42,960
他等了很久了
He's waited a long time.

491
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:46,210
至少让她有个总统的样儿
Let her at least look like the president.

492
00:27:47,670 --> 00:27:50,280
之后如果有必要  我会搅黄她的提名人
I'll scuttle the nomination if it comes to that later.

493
00:27:51,140 --> 00:27:53,710
是我要阿布佐法官  马克
I want Judge Abruzzo, Mark.

494
00:27:53,910 --> 00:27:55,890
永远别质疑我哥哥能不能
And don't ever question my brother's ability

495
00:27:55,890 --> 00:27:58,320
发挥最大的本事
to function at the highest level.

496
00:28:00,990 --> 00:28:03,130
西尔维娅·普拉斯[作家]那句话怎么说的
What is that Sylvia Plath line?

497
00:28:03,830 --> 00:28:06,030
"她像吸气一般吞食男人"
"She eats men like air."

498
00:28:06,220 --> 00:28:07,870
这是说谁呢
Who are we talking about?

499
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:20,270
抱歉我们昨天没碰到
Sorry we missed each other yesterday.

500
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:23,550
很抱歉今天又要让你为难了
Well, my apologies for leaving you in the lurch again today.

501
00:28:23,550 --> 00:28:24,600
没事吧
Everything okay?

502
00:28:24,650 --> 00:28:25,990
我跟安奈特谈过了
I spoke to Annette.

503
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:28,390
我真心认为这是最佳办法
I really think this is the best course.

504
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:32,460
-你见过乔治吗  -谁
- Did you ever meet George? - George?

505
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:36,650
我弟弟乔治  平凡的乔治
My brother George. Incurious George.

506
00:28:36,650 --> 00:28:37,890
不  没见过
No, I never did.

507
00:28:38,230 --> 00:28:39,090
想当年
And back in the old days,

508
00:28:39,090 --> 00:28:41,650
我们在中西部买下了一个厂子
we acquired an operation in the Midwest,

509
00:28:41,650 --> 00:28:43,550
精炼加拿大原油
refining Canadian crude.

510
00:28:43,630 --> 00:28:45,280
利润...
Profit margin was...

511
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:47,270
令人吃惊
It was staggering.

512
00:28:47,270 --> 00:28:48,360
但乔治
But George,

513
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:51,690
却突然崇高了起来
he got all high-minded about it.

514
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:56,340
觉得我们违法太多  于是
Thought that we were bending too many laws. So he--

515
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:59,970
他买下了一家对手公司  环保能源的那种
He bought a rival company, green energy type,

516
00:28:59,970 --> 00:29:01,330
然后起诉了我们
and he sued us.

517
00:29:02,150 --> 00:29:03,400
起诉我们啊
Sued us.

518
00:29:03,970 --> 00:29:05,000
真是的
I mean...

519
00:29:05,570 --> 00:29:06,870
这样的背叛
The betrayal.

520
00:29:07,940 --> 00:29:11,770
我父亲真正信仰的  是家庭
My father's true religion was family.

521
00:29:12,330 --> 00:29:13,720
他很心寒
And he was troubled.

522
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:16,660
他对乔治的所作所为非常心寒
He was deeply troubled by what George had done.

523
00:29:16,660 --> 00:29:17,930
改了遗嘱
Changed his will.

524
00:29:18,900 --> 00:29:20,660
他死前
Any sibling bringing litigation

525
00:29:20,660 --> 00:29:23,690
任何起诉过其他兄妹的子女
against any other at the time of his death

526
00:29:23,690 --> 00:29:26,610
将自动失去他或她的那份遗产
would automatically lose their share of the inheritance.

527
00:29:26,810 --> 00:29:28,820
每一分该死的钱
Every damnable penny.

528
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:31,360
他就这么说的
He used that word.

529
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,770
而乔治就这样失去了继承权
Which is exactly what happened to George.

530
00:29:36,010 --> 00:29:37,610
他不敢相信
George couldn't believe it.

531
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,760
还说是我哄骗爸爸那么做的
Accused me of tricking Dad into doing it

532
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:43,170
因为他已经虚弱得神志不清了
when he was too weak to know his own mind.

533
00:29:43,170 --> 00:29:47,110
我父亲心里从来都很清楚
My father always knew his own mind.

534
00:29:47,860 --> 00:29:48,800
乔治
George...

535
00:29:50,570 --> 00:29:53,250
他伤心透了
...he was just so broken up about it.

536
00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:57,190
都没对遗嘱做出抗争
Didn't even contest the will.

537
00:29:57,710 --> 00:29:58,860
而在我看来
Which as far as I see it,

538
00:29:58,860 --> 00:30:00,480
这意味着他就不配
it means he had no place inheriting

539
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:02,530
继承那样的钱
that kind of money to begin with.

540
00:30:03,310 --> 00:30:06,400
他本来有他所需要的一切
The man had everything he ever needed.

541
00:30:06,850 --> 00:30:08,070
但他太...
He was just so...

542
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,650
短视
Short-sighted.

543
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:15,450
现在住在缅因州的一个岛上
Lives on some island in Maine now.

544
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:18,300
知道对于我来说最糟的部分是什么吗
You know what the worst part for me was?

